---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Semantic Layer - Drizby"
  description="The semantic layer is powered by drizzle-cube. It compiles Drizzle ORM schemas into analytics cubes."
  ogImage="https://www.drizby.com/images/drizby_5.png"
  canonicalPath="/features/semantic-layer"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://www.drizby.com" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Features", "item": "https://www.drizby.com/#features" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Semantic Layer", "item": "https://www.drizby.com/features/semantic-layer" }
    ]
  })} />
  <main class="feature-page">
    <a href="/" class="breadcrumb">&larr; Back to Home</a>

    <section class="hero hero-img-right">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1>Semantic Layer</h1>
        <p class="hero-desc">Define your metrics once. Query them everywhere — dashboards, APIs, or AI agents. Powered by drizzle-cube.</p>
        <ul class="hero-highlights">
          <li>Code-first cubes built on your existing Drizzle ORM schemas</li>
          <li>AI-assisted cube generation from database introspection</li>
          <li>Consistent metric definitions across every query surface</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://cloud.drizby.com/register" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Try Drizby Cloud</a>
          <a class="btn" href="https://try.drizzle-cube.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Try Drizzle-Cube Playground</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-visual">
        <img src="/images/drizby-cubes.png" alt="Semantic layer cubes" loading="eager" />
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Built on drizzle-cube</h2>
        <p>drizzle-cube sits between your queries and the database, translating cube queries to SQL with security context enforcement. It provides a unified analytics API on top of your existing Drizzle ORM schemas, so you never have to write raw SQL for analytics again.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">How it works</h2>

      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-step-header">
          <span class="step-number">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Generate schemas from your database</h3>
            <p>Connect your database and Drizby introspects it to generate Drizzle ORM schemas directly from your existing tables. No manual schema writing required — just point at your database and go.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="screenshot-container">
          <figure>
            <img src="/images/drizby-schema.png" alt="Drizby schema editor" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Auto-generate Drizzle schemas from your existing database</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-connector">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 2 40" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"><line x1="1" y1="0" x2="1" y2="40" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4 4" opacity="0.3"/></svg>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-step-header">
          <span class="step-number">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Define analytics cubes</h3>
            <p>Add measures (count, sum, avg), dimensions (columns, time), and joins to create a queryable semantic model. Or let AI generate cube definitions from your schemas automatically.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="screenshot-container">
          <figure>
            <img src="/images/drizby-cubes.png" alt="Drizby cube definitions" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>Build analytics cubes on top of your schemas</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-connector">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 2 40" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"><line x1="1" y1="0" x2="1" y2="40" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4 4" opacity="0.3"/></svg>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-step-header">
          <span class="step-number">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Query everywhere</h3>
            <p>Access your cubes through the REST API, dashboards, analysis builder, notebooks, or AI agents via MCP. Every query goes through the semantic layer with security context enforcement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Full IDE Experience</h3>
          <p>Monaco editor with TypeScript autocomplete for Drizzle ORM and drizzle-cube types. Real-time compilation with inline error reporting. Write cubes with the same DX as VS Code.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>AI-Powered Cube Generation</h3>
          <p>Point AI at your schemas and it generates cube definitions automatically. Supports Anthropic Claude, OpenAI, and Google Gemini for intelligent cube scaffolding.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Flexible Security Context</h3>
          <p>Apply any row-level constraint in TypeScript — group membership, tenant isolation, user roles, and more. Every cube query passes through the semantic layer with a security context you define, so access boundaries are enforced at the query layer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Database Introspection</h3>
          <p>Auto-generate Drizzle schemas from existing databases. Connect to PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, or any supported database and pull in table definitions instantly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section cta-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Get Started</h2>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/cliftonc/drizby" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <svg class="gh-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor"><path d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.013 8.013 0 0016 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"/></svg>
          Drizby on GitHub
        </a>
        <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/cliftonc/drizzle-cube" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <svg class="gh-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor"><path d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.013 8.013 0 0016 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"/></svg>
          drizzle-cube
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .feature-page {
    max-width: 1150px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }
  .breadcrumb:hover { color: var(--accent-hover); }

  .hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }
  .hero-img-left {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  }
  .hero-content {
    text-align: left;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .hero-desc {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 480px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .hero-highlights {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }
  .hero-highlights li {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .hero-highlights li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.45rem;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
  }
  .hero-cta {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .hero-visual {
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    box-shadow: 0 16px 40px -10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
  }
  .hero-visual img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .card:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
  .card h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .card h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .card p { color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  .flow-step {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .flow-step-header {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .flow-step-header h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .flow-step-header p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .step-number {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    min-width: 2rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: 0.1rem;
  }
  .flow-connector {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    height: 2.5rem;
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }
  .flow-connector svg {
    width: 2px;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .features-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

.screenshot-container figure {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }
  .screenshot-container figure:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(8, 145, 178, 0.1);
  }
  .screenshot-container img { width: 100%; display: block; }
  .screenshot-container figcaption {
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-section { text-align: center; }
  .cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
  }
  .btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--text); }
  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent);
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-hover);
    border-color: var(--accent-hover);
    color: #fff;
  }
  .gh-icon { width: 1em; height: 1em; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero, .hero-img-left {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }
    .hero-img-left .hero-visual {
      order: -1;
    }
    .hero-content {
      text-align: center;
    }
    .hero-highlights {
      max-width: 400px;
      margin-left: auto;
      margin-right: auto;
    }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .features-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
